<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,151,294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,151,177]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks</emphasis>
. This relatively poorly known monotypic genus is recorded from the Indo-West Pacific (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima, M. &amp; Hove, H. A. ten" box="[151,461,190,216]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="35 - 66" refId="ref62002" refString="Imajima, M. &amp; Hove, H. A. ten (1984) Serpulinae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Truk Islands, Ponape and Majuro Atoll, with some other new Indo-Pacific records. Proceedings of the Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, 27, 35 - 66." type="journal article" year="1984">Imajima &amp; ten Hove 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nishi, E." box="[474,608,190,216]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="145 - 148" refId="ref64961" refString="Nishi, E. (1993) Occurrence of Dasynema chrysogyrus Grube, 1876 (Serpulidae, Polychaeta) on the living coral Goniopora sp., at Zampa Cape, Okinawa. Nanki-seibutu, the Nanki Biological Society, 35, 145 - 148." type="journal article" year="1993">
<collectingRegion box="[474,537,190,216]" country="Serbia" name="Nis" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Nishi</collectingRegion>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
). Its characteristic feature, outwardly directed stylodes on the radioles, is unique for serpulids. Paired stylodes are found elsewhere only in the sabellid genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolliker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1217,1383,229,254]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Branchiomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1383,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Branchiomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jones" authorityYear="1962" box="[151,400,268,293]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellidae" genus="Pseudobranchiomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,400,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Pseudobranchiomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See also discussion by 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima, M. &amp; Hove, H. A. ten" box="[684,1015,268,294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="35 - 66" refId="ref62002" refString="Imajima, M. &amp; Hove, H. A. ten (1984) Serpulinae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Truk Islands, Ponape and Majuro Atoll, with some other new Indo-Pacific records. Proceedings of the Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, 27, 35 - 66." type="journal article" year="1984">Imajima &amp; ten Hove (1984)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
